  "prompt": "Can Google help me track my lost Android phone by the IMEI number?",
  "response": "Google does not use IMEI numbers to help track lost Android phones. Instead, you can track your lost Android device using Google's \"Find My Device\" feature, which requires that you have previously set it up on your device. Here's how it typically works:\n\n1. **Find My Device**: Go to the Find My Device website (https://www.google.com/android/find) or use the Find My Device app on another Android device.\n2. **Log In**: Sign in with the Google account that is associated with the lost Android phone.\n3. **Locate Your Phone**: If your phone is turned on, connected to the internet, and has location services enabled, it should show up on the map.\n\nRemember that you might not be able to track your device without this setup beforehand, and you will need access to your Google account.\n\nIf your phone has been lost or stolen, you may also consider reporting it to your mobile carrier and local authorities, as they can sometimes block the device using its IMEI number. However, this varies by carrier and jurisdiction.",
